results.title: Seattle will offer $800 grocery store vouchers to 6,000 families
results.summary: Seattle Mayor Jenny Durkan announced that the city will provide more than 6,000 families $800 in vouchers for any Safeway store in the state, according to a statement from the mayor’s office.

results.title: Spain coronavirus deaths approach 500
results.summary: Coronavirus cases in Spain have risen to 11,178 with 491 deaths, a health ministry official said Tuesday.

results.title: IKEA to shut all stores in Germany
results.summary: Furniture dealer Ikea will close all 53 of its stores in Germany from Tuesday in order to protect employees and inhibit the spread of coronavirus, the company confirmed in a statement sent to CNN.

results.title: Iran confirms largest jump in virus cases over 24-hour period
results.summary: Iran has confirmed 1,178 new cases of coronavirus, the biggest increase the country has seen over a 24-hour period.

results.title: France goes into lockdown after Macron promises to protect businesses
results.summary: France officially entered lockdown at midday Tuesday local time (7 a.m. ET) as part of a number of measures announced by President Emmanuel Macron.

results.title: 8 former passengers on the Grand Princess cruise ship have returned home to Nebraska
results.summary: Eight Nebraska residents who were passengers on the Grand Princess cruise ship returned back home Monday, according to a news release from the state's department of health.

results.title: UK warns coronavirus outbreak spreading faster than expected
results.summary: The British government has warned that the coronavirus outbreak is spreading faster than it initially predicted, London Mayor Sadiq Khan said Tuesday.

results.title: German health agency raises virus risk level and says it doesn't yet know what death rate will be
results.summary: Germany's Robert Koch Institute (RKI), the national agency for disease control and prevention, has raised the risk of the coronavirus to public health to “high.”

results.title: Airbus to temporarily halt production in Spain and France
results.summary: Airbus said Tuesday that it will “temporarily pause production and assembly activities” at sites in France and Spain for the next four days as part of efforts to contain Europe’s coronavirus outbreak.

results.title: 伊朗累计确诊16169例新冠肺炎
results.summary: 【#伊朗累计确诊16169例新冠肺炎# #伊朗新增1178例新冠肺炎#】伊朗卫生部3月17日宣布，过去一天伊朗境内新增新冠肺炎感染者1178例，累计16169例，新增死亡135例，累计988例，已有5389人治愈。（人民日报记者周輖）
